```sql
-- Staging layer: raw transactions with customer and store details
SELECT
    t.transaction_id,
    t.customer_id,
    t.store_id,
    t.amount,
    t.transaction_date,
    c.name,
    c.email,
    c.signup_date,
    COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
    COALESCE(s.region, '(unknown)') AS region
FROM transactions t
LEFT JOIN customers c
    ON c.customer_id = t.customer_id
LEFT JOIN stores s
    ON s.store_id = t.store_id
```

-- Staging layer: customer channel attributions

FROM customer_channels
```

-- int_deduped_channels.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate layer: one channel per customer (most recent attribution)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        attributed_at,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    COALESCE(channel, '(unknown)') AS channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- fct_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
```sql
-- Fact table: customer revenue aggregated by attribution channel and store city
WITH transactions_with_channels AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.amount,
        t.city,
        c.channel
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }} c
        ON c.customer_id = t.customer_id
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM transactions_with_channels
GROUP BY
    channel,
    city
ORDER BY
    channel,
    city
